body:
Initialization of arrays in SystemVerilog is allowed with `'{default: value}`. Icarus generates an invalid syntax error when this is used.

Tested against git master version 875431a3 from Feb 18, 2020.

Example code:
```systemverilog
module test;

    localparam INIT_FILE = "test.dat";
    localparam ADDR_WIDTH_BITS = 8;

    //memory array
    logic [31:0] mem [2**ADDR_WIDTH_BITS];

    //initialize memories
    initial begin
        //zero init
        mem = '{default: 0};
        //read file
        $readmemb(INIT_FILE, mem);
    end

endmodule
```
Compiled with `iverilog -tnull -g2012 test.sv`.

Error message is:
```
test.sv:12: syntax error
test.sv:12: error: malformed statement
```

